  "title": "Senior Network Engineer (Shift Duty)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Manage, monitor, and support enterprise network and security infrastructure.</li><li>Perform upgrades, patching, hardening, and performance tuning.</li><li>Support projects, system changes, and production releases.</li><li>Provide second-level incident, problem, and disaster recovery support.</li><li>Maintain network configurations, capacity planning, and documentation.</li><li>Participate in 24/7 shift-based operations.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in IT or related field, with 5+ years of network engineering experience.</li><li>Strong hands-on experience with routers, switches, firewalls, VPNs, and DNS.</li><li>Experience with cloud environments and data centre operations.</li><li>Strong troubleshooting, communication, and teamwork skills.</li><li>Able to manage multiple tasks in a high-availability environment.</li><li>Network or security certifications are a plus.</li></ul>",
